{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/malaria/background-information/complications/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e7fbe927-f840-59a4-8e00-106c2834620c","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field b3af3c78-3bf4-42a9-9f75-480a9e62ae90 --><h2>What are the complications?</h2><!-- end field b3af3c78-3bf4-42a9-9f75-480a9e62ae90 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 31fd8d76-929f-4330-98a3-b7c3d62857d3 --><!-- begin field b8e8bab6-d400-4d07-9348-aad1dd7892cb --><ul><li><strong>Complications of malaria include:</strong><ul><li>Cerebral malaria — severe malaria due to <em>P. falciparum</em> with coma (<a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/background-information/complications/#glasgow-blantyre-coma-score\">Glasgow coma score</a> less than 11 or <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/background-information/complications/#glasgow-blantyre-coma-score\">Blantyre coma score</a> less than 3) or malaria with coma persisting for more than 30 minutes after a seizure.</li><li>Acute respiratory distress syndrome.</li><li>Spontaneous bleeding and coagulopathy.</li><li>Septicaemia.</li><li>Severe anaemia.</li><li>Hypoglycaemia.</li><li>Metabolic acidosis.</li><li>Acute kidney injury.</li><li>Nephrotic syndrome.</li><li>Jaundice.</li><li>Splenic rupture.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>In pregnancy:</strong><ul><li>Severe malaria is more likely, particularly in the second and third trimesters, and is often associated with pulmonary oedema and hypoglycaemia.</li><li>Cerebral malaria has a mortality rate of 50% (higher than non-pregnant adults).</li><li>Foetal death, premature delivery and intrauterine growth retardation may occur.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/references/\">RCOG, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/references/\">Whitty, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/references/\">PHE, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/references/\">WHO, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/malaria/references/\">Lalloo et al, 2016</a>]</p><!-- end field b8e8bab6-d400-4d07-9348-aad1dd7892cb --><!-- end item 31fd8d76-929f-4330-98a3-b7c3d62857d3 -->","topic":{"id":"a45cc869-8a29-5718-8d8c-fb4da11e3f58","topicId":"396f54ea-4a43-432a-964a-bf1c1d1ec304","topicName":"Malaria","slug":"malaria","lastRevised":"Last revised in November 2017","chapters":[{"id":"77ca73e7-67fc-5532-afdd-8a33d4f624bc","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"1d13888f-5984-5ba7-b602-28290217579c","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47353782-3c00-592f-bb46-5aed457f620b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"c79fc9bf-9bf2-5be3-96a4-0e3a7b6c035d","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"170e13bf-3ada-54b4-b1da-bf3f2e576eff","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"edb18b0f-ecf6-511d-a62e-1a7193478cf6","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e59bc905-80b7-59af-bcf3-18c542a8d661","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"016d9462-dbe7-5825-a4d6-41fc5e8d1de3","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"712ad264-c3b5-5462-be1e-e09e84881fdd","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"641a2f83-4b03-5455-8d1f-6d262c88ef45","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"beeed4d8-0061-5d53-9a52-4d9334fb0910","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"d4ec1d6f-3615-57b6-ae2a-adb55e52ea5d","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE Quality standards"}]},{"id":"b057ab2c-b9ca-5c35-835c-b6eae8d2496a","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"498a864c-c278-5bde-b72a-027b19ecbc6e","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"13d57b0c-a8e8-5545-96f7-ee1a1c63e32a","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"866f277b-df2d-578d-b7d7-3a177101a324","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"706cfee4-7e61-51db-a06e-70897a85bb03","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"e7fbe927-f840-59a4-8e00-106c2834620c","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"0f19cdf2-1ae3-59f9-aa7e-5c62ccf99e0b","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"626cfe9a-1cdd-5ce1-b17e-aa5e34dfd463","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features"},{"id":"945266cc-cfef-5b4f-8052-2fd55963fc95","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"8001a16a-f444-515d-868e-29a0fb3d528b","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"f44c57a5-21c7-5020-af41-0c1bce84d4fb","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"1e63a1a0-efe4-5864-b436-fdab0190793f","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"9fb3ee06-d5b5-5f13-91bd-eb4f5b931651","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bcaaf29e-dba5-5a1d-95af-f33c4cb8b1ab","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"3a06d73b-b4d8-540e-b662-f35a7a79658a","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"26a9dace-bd47-561a-99a4-80a39ae3a7fc","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"13eeb1d8-0198-54d8-92a2-1af0e30acbef","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"7184569b-0bd0-580e-94f2-74fa8726805c","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"724d6a34-a291-5477-a333-21be291a07cb","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"ed00be2d-b5e0-51b5-ade1-2acfd1171a2b","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"b057ab2c-b9ca-5c35-835c-b6eae8d2496a","slug":"background-information","fullItemName":"Background information"},"subChapters":[{"id":"ffef3c4a-a9c3-5795-b05a-946a0f9eff25","slug":"glasgow-blantyre-coma-score","fullItemName":"Glasgow and Blantyre coma score","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field bc8cf9dd-3a9e-4e3f-853e-a6bd00fc48e7 --><h3>The Glasgow and Blantyre coma scales</h3><!-- end field bc8cf9dd-3a9e-4e3f-853e-a6bd00fc48e7 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 27dfa5bd-035f-434a-9b64-a6bd00fc4880 --><!-- begin field 1aea88a7-d7fc-45e1-b3ce-a6bd00fc48e7 --><h4>The Glasgow Coma Scale</h4><ul><li>The GCS is used to assess level of consciousness. People are scored according to their best eye, verbal, and motor responses, with the lowest possible score being 3/15 (deep coma or death), and the highest being 15/15 (fully awake).</li><li>The person's GCS score should be fully documented, with the individual scores for best eye, verbal, and motor responses stated; for example, a best score of 4 for eye response, 5 for verbal response, and 5 for motor response should be recorded as E4, V5, M5 and the total cumulative GCS score given with the denominator (15) always included (for example a score of 14/15).</li></ul><p><strong>Table 1. </strong>The GCS for adults and children who are able to talk (usually 5 years of age and older)</p><table><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">Type of response</th><th scope=\"col\">Response</th><th scope=\"col\">Score</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"4\"><strong>Best eye response</strong></td><td>Does not open eyes</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Opens eyes in response to painful stimuli</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>Opens eyes in response to voice</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>Opens eyes spontaneously</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"5\"><strong>Best verbal response</strong></td><td>Makes no sounds</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Incomprehensible sounds</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>Inappropriate words</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>Confused and disorientated</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>Orientated and converses normally</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"6\"><strong>Best motor response</strong></td><td>Makes no movement in response to pain</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Extension in response to painful stimuli</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>Abnormal flexion in response to painful stimuli</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>Withdrawal in response to painful stimuli</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>Localizes painful stimuli</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>Obeys simple commands</td><td>6</td></tr></tbody></table><h4>The Blantyre Coma Scale</h4><ul><li>The BCS is a modification of the GCS for use with children who are too young to talk.</li><li>A score of 2 or less indicates 'unrousable coma'. The maximum score is 5.</li></ul><p><strong>Table 2. </strong>The BCS for preverbal children</p><table><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">Type of response</th><th scope=\"col\">Response</th><th scope=\"col\">Score</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>Best eye movement</strong></td><td>Undirected — fails to watch or follow</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Directed — watches or follows</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"3\"><strong>Best verbal response</strong></td><td>No vocal response to painful stimulus</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Moans or abnormal cry</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Appropriate cry</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"3\"><strong>Best motor response</strong></td><td>No response or inappropriate response</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Withdraws limb from painful stimulus</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Localizes painful stimulus</td><td>2</td></tr></tbody></table><!-- end field 1aea88a7-d7fc-45e1-b3ce-a6bd00fc48e7 --><!-- end item 27dfa5bd-035f-434a-9b64-a6bd00fc4880 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}